node.text:
My friend Anny Morphee, who is not me, wanted me to post her holiday cover of "one of the least controversial and most beloved traditional Christmas Yuletide Carols of all time. Plus, who doesn't love a Zooey Deschanel classic?"

Not sure how much of this I agree with, but she's been my main betch for years so I have to support. Head to @annyshitbedroom for more of...her.

node.text: One of my many hidden talents is that I can keep my eyes open for 20 seconds straight. Another is my insane ability to find friends the perfect gift. Watch as I give the talented up-and-comer Catherine O’Hara some truly incredible advice as @hudsonsbay bay’s Gifting Guru. www.thebay.com/holiday #HBHoliday #ad

node.text: I'm named Anne. I'm good at things like watching TV for a really long time and dipping things in tzatziki. My friend @bossieperson is also named Anne. She is good at things like animating this @andyshauf video frame by frame and teaching her puppy to communicate in English. I don't want to say there's a superior Anne? But..

node.text:
My Bostonian friend @kristen_barry_mcneil gave me this elegant can of mace as a wrap gift. I hope so much that none of you ever have to use a can of mace, but if you do, please follow Kristen's advice:
.
"Ok listen.  If you gotta use it, none of this *makes very sad and pathetic noises* bullshit. You just gotta be like MOTHAAAAFUCKAAAAAAAAH!!! and empty the whole fuckin thing."
.
Not entirely sure why they don't put this on the package.

node.text: So proud of my sweet friends who won, and helped me win a SAG (Smells Amazing, Guys!) award last night. I'm not sure how I got one due to the fact that I insist on wearing natural deodorant and was laughed at every day on set for smelling bad, but I'll take it! Thanks for collectively masking my scent, my loves. I MISS YOU.
